{"lemma":"جَرادٌ","slug":"جَرادٌ","root":"ج.ر.د","root_slug":"ج-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جَراد","root":"جرد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5477","n5483"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"locusts, vegetation clearing insects","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"فَأَرْسَلْنَا عَلَيْهِمُ ٱلطُّوفَانَ وَٱلْجَرَادَ وَٱلْقُمَّلَ وَٱلضَّفَادِعَ وَٱلدَّمَ آيَاتٍ مُفَصَّلَاتٍ فَٱسْتَكْبَرُوا وَكَانُوا قَوْمًا مُجْرِمِينَ","english":"We caused to be sent upon them destruction abounding, locusts, lice, frogs, and the blood, as signs of proof discernibly clear, but they had considered themselves of greater importance and had been a people who caused wrongdoing to be encouraged."},{"text":"خُشَّعًا أَبْصَارُهُمْ يَخْرُجُونَ مِنَ ٱلْأَجْدَاثِ كَأَنَّهُمْ جَرَادٌ مُّنْتَشِرٌ","english":"Their eyes humbled, they will emerge from the graves as if they were locusts spreading."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"locusts, vegetation clearing insects; a person or thing who absconds with or divests a thing from a person","tags":["collective","figuratively"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grasshoppers by comparison","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/d͡ʒa.raːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5477","headword_ar":"جَرَادٌ","root":"jrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[a coll. gen. n., (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Locusts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"locust; a kind of insect"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) so called from stripping the ground, (A, Msb,) i. e., eating what is upon it: (Msb:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jrAd","text_ar":"جراد"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) applied alike to the male and the female: (S, Msb, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jrAdp","text_ar":"جرادة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not the masc. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarN","text_ar":"بَقَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but is a [coll.] gen. n.; these two words being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarN","text_ar":"بَقَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarapN","text_ar":"بَقَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorN","text_ar":"تَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorapN","text_ar":"تَمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAmN","text_ar":"حَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAmapN","text_ar":"حَمَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.: it is therefore necessary that the masc. should be [in my copies of the S, “should not be,” but this is corrected in the margin of one of those copies,] of the same form as the fem., lest it should be confounded with the pl. [or rather the collective form]: (S:) but some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jrAd","text_ar":"جراد"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the masc.; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jrAdp","text_ar":"جرادة"},{"kind":"text","text":", the fem.; and the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayatu jaraAdFA EalaY jaraAdapK","text_ar":"رَاَيَتُ جَرَادًا عَلَى جَرَادَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw a male locust upon a female locust"},{"kind":"text","text":"], like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu naEaAmFA EalaY naEaAmapK","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ نَعَامًا عَلَى نَعَامَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is cited: (TA:) it is first called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sirowapN","text_ar":"سِرْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dabFY","text_ar":"دَبًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gawogaA='u","text_ar":"غَوْغَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":407},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayofaAnN","text_ar":"خَيْفَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuitofaAnN","text_ar":"كُِتْفَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jrAd","text_ar":"جراد"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A 'Obeyd, TA:) As says that when the males become yellow and the females become black, they cease to have any name but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jrAd","text_ar":"جراد"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AHn, TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu","text_ar":"اِبْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaraAdi","text_ar":"الجَرَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":") or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abn AljaraAdapi","text_ar":"ابن الجَرَادَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in that art.,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The egg of the locust."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T and TA ubi suprà.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^adoriY A^aY~u jaraAdK EaArahu","text_ar":"مَا اَدْرِى اَىُّ جَرَادٍ عَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~u AljaraAdi","text_ar":"اَىُّ الجَرَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, L,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I know not what man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","A","TA","L"]},{"entry_id":"n5483","headword_ar":"جَرَّادٌ","root":"jrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who polishes brazen vessels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}